cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.RO 

This paper discusses the evolution of complexity in an artificial life system, which involves neural networks and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves artificial intelligence and machine learning techniques, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of robots in experiments, which suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper touches on the broader question of evolutionary trends, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics and Automation).
